<a href="http://Ayonae.Ro">Ayonae.Ro</a> Server Community Board</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujboone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jboone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/16/01 6:31:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Divine Legion Will Be in Hate Sat 1pm EST</span><hr size=1> There is no problem with coordinating a guild Raid. Where 2 guilds are in hate or any plane at the same time.. It just seems a little disrespectful to me to have posted a raid just to have some other guild tell me that there going up at the same time and that if we want to work something out with them to post on Their boards..  <p>Booney (52nd Druid of Tunare)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uusulson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Usulson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/16/01 7:10:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Divine Legion Will Be in Hate Sat 1pm EST</span><hr size=1> I know no one owns a Plane, and cannot reserve it exclusively.  However, I have seen two guilds get embroiled in nasty, ugly, and heated debate prior and post the breaking of a Plane.  It always gets ugly, and everyone leaves hacked off. All I am saying is if you saw that someone was planning on raiding a plane, then you should contact the leader of that said guild, and coordinate something mutually agreeable, versus changing your planned raid time to &quot;mystically&quot; mirror our break time.  It is inconsiderate, because it puts us in the position of being rushed, and racing you to desired mobs and loot. Hell I don't even know if my new guild can break Hate, but I would like to go at our own pace versus being pushed out of our comfort zone.<br>
<br>
&lt;emote&gt; maybe I just had some bad muffins for breakfast &lt;grumble&gt; &lt;grumble&gt; <br>
<br>
 <br>
